Script,BasicWhatToOpen
window.currentPBSScenario = 'BasicWhatToOpen';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Basic_What_To_Open';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for BasicWhatToOpen');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'BasicWhatToOpen',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1[CDHSN]
*/
ntShape = shape(south,any 4333 + any 4432 + any 5332 - 5xxx -x5xx)

oN = hcp(south)>14 and hcp(south)<18 and ntShape
tN = hcp(south)>19 and hcp(south)<22 and ntShape

# Predict South's Opening suit
# What's the longest suit?
s = spades(south)
h = hearts(south)
d = diamonds(south)
c = clubs(south)
oS = s>4 and s>=h and s>=d and s>=c             and not (oN or tN)
oH = not oS and h>4 and h>=d and h>=c           and not (oN or tN)
oD = not (oS or oH) and ((d>3 and d>=c) or c<3) and not (oN or tN)
oC = not (oS or oH or oD) and c>3               and not (oN or tN)

# Standard 1-of-suit opening range
sHcp = hcp(south) > 11 and hcp(south) < 22

# Quiet opponents and partner so the focus is on the opening choice
nHcp = hcp(north) >= 0 and hcp(north) < 14
eHcp = hcp(east) < 11
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

oS or oH or oD or oC or oN or tN and sHcp

action printoneline,
average "1C " 100 * oC,
average "1D " 100 * oD,
average "1H " 100 * oH,
average "1S " 100 * oS,
average "1N " 100 * oN,
average "1T " 100 * tN,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Basic What to Open,\n\
--- Basic: What Should I Open? (beginner)\n\
South has a typical opening hand (12-21 HCP). The challenge: pick the\n\
right opening bid.\n\
\n\
Decision tree:\n\
• 15-17 HCP balanced (4-3-3-3，4-4-3-2，or 5-3-3-2 with 5-card minor) → 1NT\n\
• Open the longest five-card or longer suit at the one-level. If you have two\n\
  suits that are the same length，open the higher ranked.\n\
• Open 1♦ if you have four diamonds and four or fewer clubs.\n\
• Open 1♦ if your shape is exactly 4=4=3=2.\n\
• Otherwise，Open 1♣.\n\
This is a mixture scenario covering all 1-level openings. No 2!C strong,\n\
no preempts，no passed hands.\n\
https://pfdubois.github.io/BridgeBidding/Opening.html#choosing-an-opening-bid\n\
%BasicWhatToOpen%
